{
  "texts": [
    "However, privacy also encompasses aspects of one's physical being, home, and lifestyle.",
    "As an immersive and often embodied experience, IXR brings elements of physical privacy into the virtual domain.",
    "It facilitates the flow of information within our broader information environment; in more philosophical terms, IXR tends to lower the ontological friction in the infosphere (Floridi, 2005).",
    "Thus, it cannot be regulated solely as a matter of data and communications privacy.",
    "In the early days of VR and AR, privacy was often an afterthought or disregarded."
  ]
}